      "value": "What are Function Types?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Function types define the structure of a function, including its parameters and return type."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Function Type"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "let add: (a: number, b: number) => number;\n\nadd = (x, y) => x + y;"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using Type Alias"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type AddFn = (a: number, b: number) => number;\n\nconst sum: AddFn = (a, b) => a + b;"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using Interface"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "interface MultiplyFn {\n  (a: number, b: number): number;\n}\n\nconst multiply: MultiplyFn = (a, b) => a * b;"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
